Break-out superstar, Shekhinah had the night of her life on Saturday night at the 24th annual South African Music Awards held in Sun City, North West. The Suited and Please Mr hit-make scooped three major awards at the glittering award ceremony. She took home Newcomer of the Year, Album of the Year and Female Artist of the Year awards for the sterling work on her debut album Rose Gold. After winning her first award (Newcomer), Shekhinah spoke about what a momentous occasion SAMA24 was for her. “It took me five years to win this award,” she said. The Durban-born star thanked her loyal fans and her team for their undying support of her work. Fans and fellow celebs have expressed their pride and adoration of the singer on social media.  